body_content.explanation: (especially of things that are not living) being a large distance from top to bottom or a long way above the ground, or having the stated distance from top to bottom:
examples: a high building/mountain
high ceilings
It's two and a half metres high and one metre wide.
The corn grew waist-high (= as high as a person's waist) in the fields.

body_content.explanation: greater than the usual level or amount:
examples: The job demands a high level of concentration.
He suffers from high blood pressure.
Antique furniture fetches very high prices these days.
She got very high marks in her geography exam.
It's very dangerous to drive at high speed when the roads are wet.
He's in a high-security prison.

body_content.explanation: containing a large quantity of something:
examples: I avoid foods that are high in fat.

body_content.explanation: very good or very moral standards:
examples: She was a woman of high principles.
High winds caused delays on the ferries.

body_content.explanation: having power, an important position, or great influence:
examples: an officer of high rank

body_content.explanation: near or at the top of the range of sounds:
examples: I can't reach the high notes.

body_content.explanation: (of food) smelling bad and no longer good to eat:
examples: This meat is rather high - I'm going to throw it out.

body_content.explanation: not thinking or behaving normally because of taking drugs:
examples: He was high on heroin at the time.

body_content.explanation: a higher level than has ever been reached previously:
examples: Interest rates have reached an all-time/record high.

body_content.explanation: a period of extreme excitement or happiness when you feel full of energy, often caused by a feeling of success, or by drugs or alcohol or a religious experience:
examples: Exercise gives you a high.
She's been on a high ever since she got her article published in the Times.
There are lots of highs and lows in this job.

body_content.explanation:
informal for
high school  (when used in the name of a school):
examples: I go to Santa Ana High.

body_content.explanation: at or to a large distance from the ground:
examples: You'll have to hit the ball quite high to get it over that net.
The new jet flew much higher than most planes.
